The Cross River state police command has confirmed the arrest and commencement of investigation into the arrest of Sergeants Ayade Vincent, Okoi Otu and four other suspects, for allegedly stealing about 64 cartons of Tiles, from the Canadian University Obudu, Cross River State. A statement by the state Police Public Relations Officer, PPRO, SP Irene Ugbo, revealed that the suspects are in police custody currently. “Sergeants Ayade Vincent, Okoi Otu, and four other suspects are currently in police custody for allegedly stealing Tiles, from the Canadian university, Obudu, in Cross River state. “The duo has abused or defiled their rules of engagement or extant laws of the land, hence they are currently undergoing orderly room trial, as stipulated in the police act and regulations. The police noted that, “the other four suspects, will be arraigned in court Soonest and that the outcome of the orderly trial shall determine whether or not, the charges will be amended, to include the policemen.” YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…stealing tiles  stealing tiles Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…stealing tiles  stealing tiles How Adetunji Made over N20million in 2021 from Football Trading. Click Here to Join his team